






@(1-3=c1815.1) Now the lord once decided to set off for the mountain where the man lives; Lord @wRN{Gilgameš} decided to set off for the mountain where the man lives. He spoke to his slave @wPN{Enkidu}:

@(4-7=c1815.4) @q[Gilgamec,Enkidu]{“@wPN{Enkidu}, since a man cannot pass beyond the final end of life, I want to set off into the mountains, to establish my renown there. Where renown can be established there, I will establish my renown; and where no renown can be established there, I shall establish the renown of the gods.”}

@(8-12=c1815.8) His slave @wPN{Enkidu} answered him: @q[Enkidu,Gilgamec]{“My lord, if today you are going to set off into the mountains, @wDN{Utu} should know about it from us. 
{@noteanchor{1 ms. adds:} If you are going to to set off into the @wGN{Mountains of Cedar-felling}, @wDN{Utu} should know about it from us.
} @wDN{Utu}, youthful @wDN{Utu}, should know about it from us. A decision that concerns the mountains is @wDN{Utu's} business. A decision that concerns the @wGN{Mountains of Cedar-felling} is the business of youthful @wDN{Utu}. @wDN{Utu} should know about it from us.”}

@(13-16=c1815.13) @wRN{Gilgameš} 
{prepared
} 
{@noteanchor{2 mss. have instead:} took hold of
}  a white kid. 
{He clasped a brown kid, a sacrificial animal, close to his breast.
} 
{@noteanchor{1 ms. has instead:} He …… a brown kid.
}  In his hand he held a holy staff before his nose, as he addressed @wDN{Utu} of heaven:


@(17-18=c1815.17) @q[Gilgamec,Utu]{“@wDN{Utu}, I am going to set off into the mountains! May you be my helper! I am going to set off into the @wGN{Mountains of Cedar-felling}! May you be my helper!”}

@(19-20=c1815.19) From heaven @wDN{Utu} replied to him: @q[Utu,Gilgamec]{“Young man, you are noble already in your own right -- but what would you want with the mountains?”}

@(21-33=c1815.21) @q[Gilgamec,Utu]{“@wDN{Utu}, I have something to say to you -- a word in your ear! I greet you -- please pay attention! In my city people are dying, and hearts are full of distress. People are lost -- that fills me with 
{@noteanchor{1 ms. adds:} wretched
}  dismay. I craned my neck over the city wall: corpses in the water make the river almost overflow. That is what I see. That will happen to me too -- that is the way things go. No one is tall enough to reach heaven; no one can reach wide enough to stretch over the mountains. Since a man cannot pass beyond the final end of life, I want to set off into the mountains, to establish my renown there. Where renown can be established there, I will establish my renown; and where no renown can be established there, I shall establish the renown of the gods.”}

@(34-47=c1815.34) @wDN{Utu} accepted his tears as a fitting gift. As befits a compassionate person, he turned to him full of compassion: @q[Utu,Gilgamec]{“Now there are seven warriors, sons of a single mother. The first, their eldest brother, has lion's paws and eagle's talons. The second is a …… snake, ……. The third is a dragon snake, ……. The fourth blazes with fire ……. The fifth is a …… snake, ……. The sixth
{@noteanchor{1 ms. adds:}, a shackle that …… the rebel lands in the hills,
