@(68-75=c1815.68) @wRN{Gilgameš} …… was overcome by sleep, and it affected @wPN{Enkidu} …… as a powerful longing. His fellow-citizens who had come with him flailed around at his feet like puppies. @wPN{Enkidu} awoke from his dream, shuddering from his sleep. He rubbed his eyes; there was eery silence everywhere. He touched @wRN{Gilgameš}, but could not rouse him. He spoke to him, but he did not reply.

@(76-84=c1815.76) @q[Enkidu,Gilgamec]{“You who have gone to sleep, you who have gone to sleep! @wRN{Gilgameš}, young lord of @wSN{Kulaba}, how long will you sleep for? The mountains are becoming indistinct as the shadows fall across them; the evening twilight lies over them. Proud @wDN{Utu} has already gone to the bosom of his mother @wDN{Ningal}. @wRN{Gilgameš}, how long will you sleep for? The sons of your city who came with you should not have to wait at the foot of the hills. Their own mothers should not have to twine string in the square of your city.”}

