@(92-95=c1815.92) A second time he spoke to him: @q[Gilgamec,Enkidu]{“By the life of my own mother @wDN{Ninsumun} and of my father, holy @wDN{Lugalbanda}! Until I discover whether that person was a human or a god, I shall not direct back to the city my steps which I have directed to the mountains.”}

@(96-97=c1815.96) The slave, trying to ameliorate the situation, trying to make life appear more attractive, answered his master:

